# INITIAL CODEBASE RULES
## CORE PHILOSOPHY
Zero-friction onboarding, strict environment isolation, and minimal initial footprint.

## DIRECTORY & SCAFFOLDING
- Enforce strict separation of concerns: isolate `src/`, `tests/`, `docs/`, and `config/`.
- Maintain a single source of truth for all configuration values.
- Abstract environment variables; require a `.env.example` or equivalent schema template.
- Implement strict path aliasing to avoid deep relative imports.

## DEPENDENCY MANAGEMENT
- Adopt a zero-trust dependency model: minimize external libraries. Justify every addition.
- Lock all dependency versions explicitly to guarantee deterministic builds.
- Separate runtime dependencies strictly from build/development dependencies.

## PIPELINE & AUTOMATION PREPARATION
- Integrate static analysis, linting, and formatting from commit zero.
- Scaffold pre-commit/pre-push hooks to enforce code standards before CI/CD.
- Ensure the project is container-ready or virtually isolated from the host OS.